				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="cp-box-container"><div class="cp-curator-box noprint"><b><u>Post-publication activity</u></b><br /><button class="cp-button btn"></button><p><span class="cp-title-label">Curator:</span> <a href="/article/User:Giovanni_Gallavotti" title="User:Giovanni Gallavotti">Giovanni Gallavotti</a>
</p><div class="cp-assistants hidden"><div><span class="cp-title-label">Contributors:</span><p>&nbsp;</p></div><div><span>0.17 - </span><p><a href="/article/User:Benjamin_Bronner" title="User:Benjamin Bronner">Benjamin Bronner</a>
</p></div><div><span>0.17 - </span><p><a href="/article/User:Juan_Pablo_Carbajal" title="User:Juan Pablo Carbajal">Juan Pablo Carbajal</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Bertrand_Duplantier" title="User:Bertrand Duplantier">Bertrand Duplantier</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Nick_Orbeck" title="User:Nick Orbeck">Nick Orbeck</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Jie_Bao" title="User:Jie Bao">Jie Bao</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Eugene_M._Izhikevich" title="User:Eugene M. Izhikevich">Eugene M. Izhikevich</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Leo_Trottier" title="User:Leo Trottier">Leo Trottier</a>
</p></div><div><span></span><p><a href="/article/User:Joel_L._Lebowitz" title="User:Joel L. Lebowitz">Joel L. Lebowitz</a>
</p></div></div></div></div><div class="cp-author-order"><ul id="sp_authors"><li id="sort-1"><p><a href="/article/User:Giovanni_Gallavotti" title="User:Giovanni Gallavotti"><span class="bold">Prof. Giovanni Gallavotti</span>, INFN , University di Roma, Italy, Roma, Italy</a>
</p></li></ul></div><p><strong><span class="tex2jax_ignore">Fluctuations</span></strong>:
Deviations of the value of an observable from
its average or, also, deviations of the actual time evolution of an
observable from its average evolution in a system subject to random
forces or, simply, undergoing chaotic motion. 
</p>
